dreisoft.tresos.tresosdb.api.model.v2.systemtemplate.fibex.fibexcore.corecommunication

Interface IPduTriggering

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IEntity, IIdentifiable, IReferrable

    public interface IPduTriggering
extends IEntity, IIdentifiable
    IPduTriggering: Entity class of the tresosDB model.

    The PduTriggering describes on which channel the IPdu is transmitted. The Pdu routing by the PduR is only allowed for subclasses of IPdu. Depending on its relation to entities such channels and clusters it can be unambiguously deduced whether a fan-out is handled by the Pdu router or the Bus Interface. If the fan-out is specified between different clusters it shall be handled by the Pdu Router. If the fan-out is specified between different channels of the same cluster it shall be handled by the Bus Interface.

    GENERATED CODE. DO NOT CHANGE!

        IPdu getIPdu()
        Query the undirectional to-one association IPdu.

        Reference to the Pdu for which the PduTriggering is defined. One I-Pdu can be triggered on different channels (PduR fan-out). The Pdu routing by the PduR is only allowed for subclasses of IPdu. Nevertheless is the reference to the Pdu element necessary since the PduTriggering element is also used to specify the sending and receiving connections to EcuPorts.
